te mesoderm","Lateral plate mesoderm","Intraembryonic coelom","Gut tube"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EDuring embryonic folding, the \u003Cstrong\u003Emesoderm\u003C/strong\u003E splits into segments but does not undergo ventral folding. The \u003Cstrong\u003Eintermediate mesoderm\u003C/strong\u003E gives rise to urogenital structures. The \u003Cstrong\u003Elateral plate mesoderm\u003C/strong\u003E divides to form the somatopleure and splanchnopleure. The \u003Cstrong\u003Eintraembryonic coelom\u003C/strong\u003E forms within the lateral plate mesoderm.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Egut tube\u003C/strong\u003E forms when the flat endodermal layer folds ventrally and its lateral edges fuse in the midline. This primitive gut tube will eventually develop into the epithelial lining of the gastrointestinal tract from the foregut to the hindgut.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThis folding process occurs simultaneously with the formation of head and tail folds, converting the flat trilaminar embryonic disc into a cylindrical structure.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The primitive gut tube forms from endoderm folding during the fourth week of development","The gut tube develops into the epithelial lining of the gastrointestinal tract from the foregut to hindgut"],"references":["Gaillard R, Steegers EA, de Jongste JC, Hofman A, Jaddoe VW. Tracking of fetal growth characteristics during different trimesters and the risks of adverse birth outcomes. Int J Epidemiol. 2014 Aug;43(4):1140-53. doi: 10.1093/ije/dyu036. Epub 2014 Mar 5. PMID: 24603318; PMCID: PMC4258770","Chen X, Liu H, Li Y, Zhang W, Zhou A, Xia W, Xu S. First-trimester fetal size, accelerated growth in utero, and child neurodevelopment in a cohort study. BMC Med. 2024 Apr 29;22(1):181. doi: 10.1186/s12916-024-03390-3. PMID: 38685041; PMCID: PMC11059611","Godfrey KM, Inskip HM, Hanson MA. The long-term effects of prenatal development on growth and metabolism. Semin Reprod Med. 2011 May;29(3):257-65. doi: 10.1055/s-0031-1275518. Epub 2011 Jul 18. PMID: 21769765; PMCID: PMC3685133","Singh, V. (2022). Textbook of clinical embryology, -E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"58935"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15997"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"58935","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/58935"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-23T21:23:31+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-23T21:24:17+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8688"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"73466"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"4928","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/4928"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udca9","name":"Gastrointestinal